\title{Opposite orders}
\date{2026-06-11}
\taxon{Module}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\import{stt-macros}

\agda{
module Algebra.Order.Instances.Opposite where
}

\agda-imports{
\agda{
open import Foundations.Prelude

open import Core.Joins

open import Algebra.Poset
open import Algebra.TotalOrder
}
}

\subtree[fre-00TG]{
\title{The opposite poset}
\taxon{Definition}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\date{2026-06-11}

\p{
The \em{opposite} of a poset is the poset with the order reversed.
}

\agda{
module _ {𝓤 𝓥} {A : Type 𝓤} (P : Poset 𝓥 A) (let module P = Poset P) where

  op-is-poset : is-poset (P._≥_)
  op-is-poset .is-poset.≤-is-prop = P.≤-is-prop
  op-is-poset .is-poset.≤-refl = P.≤-refl
  op-is-poset .is-poset.≤-trans p q = P.≤-trans q p
  op-is-poset .is-poset.≤-antisym p q = P.≤-antisym q p

  Poset-op : Poset 𝓥 A
  Poset-op .Poset._≤_ = P._≥_
  Poset-op .Poset.≤-is-poset = op-is-poset
}

\p{
If we had had η-equality for the \code{is-poset} predicate then this construction
would be a judgmental involution on posets.
}
}

\subtree[fre-BCE0]{
\title{The opposite of a total order is total}
\taxon{Proposition}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\date{2026-06-11}

\agda{
module _ {𝓤 𝓥} {A : Type 𝓤} where

  op-is-total : (P : Poset 𝓥 A) → is-total-poset P → is-total-poset (Poset-op P)
  op-is-total P P-is-total i j = *-comm→ (P-is-total i j)

  TotalOrder-op : TotalOrder 𝓥 A → TotalOrder 𝓥 A
  TotalOrder-op (mk-total-order P P-is-total)
    = mk-total-order (Poset-op P) (op-is-total P P-is-total)
}
}
